Write concise update logic with Immer 

Updating nested arrays without mutation can get a little bit repetitive. Just as with objects:

Generally, you shouldn‚Äôt need to update state more than a couple of levels deep. If your state objects are very deep, you might want to restructure them differently so that they are flat.
If you don‚Äôt want to change your state structure, you might prefer to use Immer, which lets you write using the convenient but mutating syntax and takes care of producing the copies for you.

Here is the Art Bucket List example rewritten with Immer:

